               <head>Collection of hymns</head>
               
               
               
               <msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070315" rend="visible">
                  
                  
                  
                  <summary>A collection of hymns, for the most part composed by Israel Najara. </summary>
                  
                  
                  
                  <textLang mainLang="he"/>
                  
                  
                  
                  <msItem rend="">
                     
                     
                     
                     <locus from="1r" to="211v"/>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">She᾿arit Yisra᾿el</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he">שארית ישראל</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <author>
                        
                        
                        
                        <persName xml:lang="en" key="viaf.org/viaf/51941634">Najara, Israel ben Moses</persName>
                        
                        
                        
                        <persName xml:lang="he" key="viaf.org/viaf/51941634">נג'רה, ישראל בן משה</persName>
                     
                     
                     
                     </author>
                     
                     
                     
                     <note>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>The pieces are arranged under the headings of Turkish tunes to which they were to be sung. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Folios 3r-18r contain a table of contents, arranged alphabetically. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Folios 211r contains some notes relating to the acrostics (of the name of the piece's author) or to the occasion of their use. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>See Benayahu, <ref target="Asufot" type="number">4</ref> (1990), pp. 256-271. </p>
                     
                     
                     
                     </note>
                  
                  
                  
                  </msItem>
               
               
               
               </msContents>
               
               
               
